Reasoning: The paper deals with the application of quantization techniques to deep reinforcement learning policies, which involves aspects of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), robotics (cs.RO), and control systems (cs.SY). The paper specifically focuses on the effects of quantization on various reinforcement learning tasks and algorithms, which falls under the purview of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The tasks involve visual inputs, such as Pong and Breakout, which are processed using computer vision techniques. The deployment of quantized policies on embedded systems also involves aspects of robotics and control systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.CV, followed by cs.RO and cs.SY.
